# Source NAT

There are three types of Source NAT in Palo Alto firewall
1. Dynamic IP and Port
2. Dynamic IP: which allows a one-to-one dynamic translation of a source IP address (without modifying the port number) to the next available address in the NAT address pool. The size of the NAT pool must match the number of internal hosts that need address translations. By default, if the number of internal hosts exceeds the size of the NAT address pool and all NAT addresses are allocated, new connections requiring address translation will be dropped.
3. Static IP

